<p>I am working on customizing a Nationbuilder theme which is built using Bootstrap CSS and Liquid. I've got everything working on all platforms except for the signup box on the header when viewed on a mobile phone is overlapping the logo. Because it is Nationbuilder, I can't modify all the containers.  This is the code in the master template file: </p>  <pre><code>&lt;body class="aware-theme v2-theme {{ page.page_class_name }} page-{{ request.template | replace: '_', '-' }} js"&gt;  {% if site.has_header_image? and page.features_count == 0 %} &lt;div class="container header-image-container"&gt;   &lt;img src="{{ site.header_image_url_1026 }}" class="header-image img-responsive" border="0" /&gt; &lt;/div&gt; {% endif %} &lt;div class="row"&gt; &lt;div class="col-sm-12 col-md-6 col-md-offset-6"&gt;&lt;br clear="all"&gt;{% subpage "join" with "homepage_signup" %}&lt;/div&gt; &lt;/div&gt; {% include "nav" %}  {% if page.features_count &gt; 0 %}   &lt;div class="container"&gt;    {% include "features" %}   &lt;/div&gt; {% endif %} </code></pre>  <p>Where it says "subpage join" is where I call in the content for the sign up box. I've tried moving this code higher in the HTML but then it disappears.</p>  <p>The content is resizing for mobile which is good but the positioning is off because the box overlaps the logo.</p>  <p>Here is the CSS for the signup box:</p>  <pre><code>.headerbox { position: absolute; z-index:99999; margin: 0px 0px 100x 0px; top:20px; border: solid 1px $theme-color-1; padding: 5px; font: $headline-font; font-size: .8em; text-align:center; } </code></pre>  <p>and this is the CSS for the logo:</p>  <pre><code>.site-logo { padding: 0; }  .navbar-brand { height: auto; padding: 0; margin-top:-30px; } .navbar { background: $header-color; margin-bottom: 0px; max-height: 190px } </code></pre>